   <div type="citation">
    <bibl><title>The American Hellenic World</title>,
<date when="1928-06">June 1928</date><title level="a">THE HYMN OF THE NEW GENERATION.</title><title level="a" type="sub">By Andrew Vlachos (translated from the Greek)</title></bibl>
   </div>
  </front>
  <body>
   <p>Sing, O New Generation!</p>
   <p>Life's sweet melody,</p>
   <p>With flowers of joy</p>
   <p>Bespangled exhilaration.</p>
   <p>Thy common Grecian start,</p>
   <p>O Maid, do not throw aside;</p>
   <p>Learn to cherish with pride</p>
   <p>"Mother Greece" in thy heart.</p>
   <p>For only then thou wilt be</p>
   <p>O Maid, a good American</p>
   <p>When thou wouldst honor, O Grecian</p>
   <p>The "Mother" of the free.</p>
   <pb facs="5422062_3_0948.jpg" n="2"/>
   <p>The "Mother" who gave birth</p>
   <p>To light that the ages endowed;</p>
   <p>The "Mother" whose renowned</p>
   <p>Parthenons fill the earth.</p>
   <p>With glory and grace abide</p>
   <p>In song, O New Generation!</p>
   <p>Of Greece, the exultation</p>
   <p>America's own pride.</p>
   <p>Thine the beauty of the dawn</p>
   <p>And glory's beauty thine;</p>
   <p>Thou, O New Generation the shrine</p>
   <p>And our country's hope to own.</p>
   <pb facs="5422062_3_0949.jpg" n="3"/>
   <p>Glory laurels will scatter</p>
   <p>Whenever thou wilt cross the land</p>
   <p>If, O New Generation, thy hand</p>
   <p>In thy oath will not falter.</p>
   <p>Hail! O Grecian maid. Hail!</p>
   <p>Greco-American glory;</p>
   <p>Hail! Thou too, our new country,</p>
   <p>And thou, O "Great Mother", hail!</p>
